            <entry xml:id="entry_g0ymīry" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>g˳ymīry</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>gumeri</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>gæmeri</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>великан</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>giant</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>дубина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>bludgeon</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>идол</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>idol</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Narty agommæ Irystony cardysty wæjgoytæ, wæjgoyty aǧommæ —
                            g.ymīrytæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>до Нартов в Осетии жили %swajyg%s’и, до %swajyg%s’ов — %sgumīry%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>before the Narts in Ossetia there lived %swajyg%s, before %swajyg%s —
                                %sgumīry%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ zærdæjæ — maxæj g˳ymīrydær næj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>нам казалось („по нашему сердцу“) — нет (людей) мощнее нас</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it seemed to us (“according to our hearts”) — there are no (people)
                                that are more powerful than us</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 60,
                            125</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>g˳ymīry adæjmag</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>грубый, неотесанный человек</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>rude, uncouth man</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>дубина</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>blockhead</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Через <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>gmiri</w>
                        <gloss><q>герой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>богатырь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>исполин</q></gloss></mentioned> восходит к племенному названию
                    древнего народа киммерийцев: <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>Κιμμέριοι</w>
                        <gloss><q>киммерийцы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="akk"><lang/>
                        <w>Gimirri</w></mentioned> (в переводе древнеперсидских надписей = Saka
                    ‘скиф’), <mentioned xml:lang="hbo"><lang/>
                        <w>Gomer</w></mentioned>. Отсюда, по-видимому, и <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>кумиръ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>кумир</w></mentioned>. Совпадение значения ‘идол’ в русском и осетинском
                    объясняется, вероятно, влиянием русского на осетинский через переводы церковных
                            книг.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>I
                            125</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSt."
                            /><biblScope>81</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It goes back to the tribal name of the ancient people of the
                    Cimmerians through <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>gmiri</w>
                        <gloss><q>hero</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>warrier</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>giant</q></gloss></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>Κιμμέριοι</w>
                        <gloss><q>Cimmerians</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="akk"><lang/>
                        <w>Gimirri</w></mentioned> (in translation of ancient Persian inscriptions =
                    Saka ‘Scythian’), <mentioned xml:lang="hbo"><lang/>
                        <w>Gomer</w></mentioned>. Apparently, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>кумиръ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>кумир</w>
                        <gloss><q>idol</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>cult figure</q></gloss></mentioned> are from it as well. The
                    identity of the ‘idol’ meaning in Russian and Ossetic is probably due to the
                    influence of Russian on Ossetian through translations of church
                            books.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>I 125</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>81</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
